    <segment id="1" parent="8" relname="concession">I agree with David Hakken that there is a need to move beyond &quot;shit shoveling.&quot;</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="8" relname="span">
My point in using the retort, &quot;So grab a shovel and join us!&quot;, was to suggest that
the STS vision of  &quot;the way forward&quot; might well be enhanced</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="2" relname="condition"> if more STSers
would take a turn or two at the shit pile. </segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="9" relname="elaboration"> This view is consistent, I think, with
Hakken&apos;s implied criticism of STSers who hesitate to &quot;get their hands 
dirty.&quot;  

